Selected Answer: BC
A is not good, because isDeleted is not indexed and != ' ' will not use index to search, 
general you want to avoid field != ' '; any negative comparison is discouraged unless there's second SELECT cause which is indexed;
B is good, because you are SELECTing from a range of ID which lower the amount of records it searches;
C is good, because even though first clause is bad, second one makes it very Selective because the field is indexed; 
D is bad because negative comparison is not encouraged
